abstract: Senators tore up their schedules over the weekend to join protesters in airport concourses and give voice to the growing fury over President Trump’s policies.
snippet: Senators tore up their schedules over the weekend to join protesters in airport concourses and give voice to the growing fury over President Trump’s policies.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Bob Casey of Pennsylvania left the Philadelphia Orchestra’s 160th annual Academy of Music Concert and Ball and rushed to Philadelphia’s airport, still clad in white tie and tails.
